name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: •Vaccinated - Do not need to quarantine. Monitor for symptoms. Get tested around day 5-7.  •Unvaccinated - Quarantine for 14-days from the last date they had close contact with the person who tested positive.  https://t.co/dqhREdesuP

name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: Tested Positive for COVID? Call US! NCHD tracks disease rates which are critical to protecting our community. In order to do this, accurate data and information needs to be collected for our region, so it is important that we record all testing. Please CALL US!!! 1-877-795-0646.  https://t.co/YB3W45cemJ

name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: Tested Positive for COVID? You can be contagious 2 days prior to symptom onset. Identifying who you were close to and notifying them is important in stopping the spread and alerting those who are high risk of getting severely sick. Learn more  https://t.co/wH7DbEEIaC  https://t.co/MGSakGaSOu

name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: Need a COVID-19 test done now? Unable to get in to see a healthcare provider? Don’t have time to visit a community testing site? At-home testing is an option. Just be sure you know what to do if you receive a positive result >>>  https://t.co/wH7DbEEIaC  https://t.co/fIdmSlCzC7

name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: Stay home if you are sick. Canceling is better than infecting those you love with COVID-19. While it’s true, most people have mild illness when getting COVID-19, there is a chance that it might be much more serious for certain family members. Read more >>>  https://t.co/tjVsGVvKZ3  https://t.co/vrwDiOTltH

name: Northeast CO Health
tweet: Be honest and don’t force yourself to push through if you don’t feel well. A fever, cough or other symptoms, might mean you have COVID-19 or some other illness. With our health system being strained, sharing any illness isn’t a good idea. Read our blog >>>  https://t.co/tjVsGVvKZ3  https://t.co/kB0g9nPfpi
